      <h1 class="h4 mb-3">13. Know how request updates relate to component sync</h1>
      <div class="tutorial-content mb-4">
        <p>If your page also uses HET components, request-driven content updates automatically dispatch the sync lifecycle that acquired component signals use.</p>
        <p>That behavior is built in, but the concept is broader than the requests module itself: component sync is useful any time some external code mutates the DOM outside normal signal bindings.</p>
        <p>The full component-side explanation, including manual <code>het:sync</code> dispatch for non-request DOM updates, is covered in the <a href="tutorial-components#10-sync-snapshot-state-after-external-dom-changes">components tutorial</a>.</p>
      </div>

